<p><div class="left-margin" id="set-C"><h2>Career</h2></div></p>

<p>It is my own observation of IT job. You may have different situations, but please take a look if you choose IT majoy solely for career.</p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Difficulty of IT job: IT advances so fast</p>

    <ul>
      <li>May require continuous learning to new technologies<br />
  IT technology advances so fast, so the knowledge of the university may not be good enough to face the challenges ahead. It looks normal to learn during, and after works.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Job nature: Need communication and hard work, while may need extra hours for support.</p>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>People may imagine being a programmer and shut the mouth off in the work. However, you may need to negotiate things with colleagues, or talk during conferences and meetings. It is quite challegeing to load the commputing logics in mind and speak human languages in mouth.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Your stand-by hours may be required to ensure system operations, which means you may have less convenience to schedule your after-work time.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<p>If you are willing to learn fast changing technologies, having good communication skills, being cooperative to others, you may consider to take IT as your career! I think the IT jobs look quite challeaging, but it depends on personal situations, and your passion to the industry.</p>

<p><br /><br /></p>
<p><div class="left-margin" id="set-D"><h2>Conclusion</h2></div></p>

<p>It would be a bit difficult to take IT as a career with only a little of interest, because it may require after-work hours. However, I think my study experience in IT major is not that bad, and I appreciate how I get trained.</p>
